  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "CHAPTER 27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ex 27:1-21. Altar for Burnt Offering.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1, 2. altar of shittim wood—The dimensions of this altar which was placed at the entrance of the sanctuary were nearly three yards square, and a yard and a half in height. Under the wooden frame of this chest-like altar the inside was hollow, and each corner was to be terminated by \"horns\"—angular projections, perpendicular or oblique, in the form of horns. The animals to be sacrificed were bound to these (Ps 118:27), and part of the blood was applied to them.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
